message.content:
A 'Polistes rubiginosus' is a species of paper wasp that belongs to the family Vespidae.
It has a reddish-brown coloration on its head, thorax and abdomen.
The thorax and abdomen are covered in a smooth, shiny texture.
The wings are transparent and veiny, with a brownish hue.
This species has a slender, elongated body, measuring around 1.5 cm in length.
Polistes rubiginosus is commonly found in North and South America, where it inhabits forests and woodlands.
As a social wasp, Polistes rubiginosus constructs nests made of paper, which can be found hanging from branches or eaves of buildings.
